Scrum Development Team 
Composition
	Developers only 
	Organization
	Self-organized, self selective of the work to do from the product backlog and how to do it 
	Cross-functional
	Self-contained with all the skills necessary to succeed
	Responsible to:
	Each team member commits their work to the team when delegated or “pulled.”  The entire team is responsible for the success/failure of the overall project.  If incorrect specifications were delivered to the team by the Product Owner, the Dev team is still responsible for successful delivery because they are to validate functionality from customer feedback during Sprint Review (delivery and feedback from the customer for that individual stage of increment development.)  Dev Team is ultimately responsible for the success/failure of the project.
	Authority
	Commit as a team to the customer 
	Size
	7 +/- 3 (too large or too small impedes progress and communication)
	

